// PX4 Renode platform — STM32H743-based, modelled on Pixhawk FMU-v6X.
//
// Extends Renode's stock `stm32h743.repl` (cloned to
// external/renode/platforms/cpus/stm32h743.repl for reference) with
// just enough peripherals for PX4 + NuttX to come up:
//
//   * Cortex-M7 + NVIC + MPU (inherited from the stock file)
//   * SysTick (inherited)
//   * USART2 — used for the pxh shell over UART
//   * The standard SRAM + flash banks (inherited)
//
// Drivers Renode doesn't model and PX4 doesn't need on this board:
// I2C, SPI, ADC, timers beyond systick, DMA, USB, ETH, FDCAN. The
// PX4 board config strips them out at the Kconfig level so the
// firmware never exercises them.
//
// Lineage of this file:
// - Vendored fragment of Renode's MIT-licensed stm32h743.repl —
//   keep the upstream copyright header below.
// - Local additions follow the BSD-3-Clause of the surrounding
//   px4-rs tree.

// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
// Copyright (c) 2010-2024 Antmicro
// (Vendored from renode/platforms/cpus/stm32h743.repl; trimmed.)

using "platforms/cpus/stm32h743.repl"

// `usart2` already exists in the upstream repl. We rebind its
// backing here so the .resc script can attach a host-side terminal
// (a pty) to it.
usart2:
    -> nvic@38
